How many different amounts can be obtained by using one or more of the coins in Dak’s collection, which consists of a quarter, a dime, a nickel, and a penny?
(A) 4
(B) 5
(C) 6
(D) 7
(E) 8
We have 4 coins: 25 cents, 10 cents, 5 cents, and 1 cent.
The question basically asks us how many different sums we can have if we can use any number of these coins: 1, 2, 3, 4, or all four coins. So, we have the following combinations:
25 cents: 1 combination;
10 cents: 1 combination;
5 cents: 1 combination;
1 cent: 1 combination;
25 + 10 cents: 1 combination;
25 + 5 cents: 1 combination;
25 + 1 cent: 1 combination;
10 + 5 cents: 1 combination;
10 + 1 cent: 1 combination;
5 + 1 cent: 1 combination;
25 + 10 + 5 cents: 1 combination;
25 + 10 + 1 cent: 1 combination;
25 + 5 + 1 cent: 1 combination;
10 + 5 + 1 cent: 1 combination;
25 + 10 + 5 + 1 cent: 1 combination.
Total: 10+1=11 different sums.
Answer: D.
